The article expresses condolences to the people of the Philippines on the death of former President Benigno Aquino III. The author describes Aquino as a valued friend and partner to the United States, and praises his integrity and dedication in serving his country. Aquino's commitment to peace, the rule of law, and economic growth for Filipinos, as well as his efforts to promote the rules-based international order, are highlighted as his lasting legacy. The author also expresses personal appreciation for their time working together and offers sympathies to Aquino's family and all who will mourn his absence.